org.gearvrf

Class GVRUnlitVerticalStereoShader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gearvrf.GVRShader
      • org.gearvrf.GVRShaderTemplate
        • org.gearvrf.GVRUnlitVerticalStereoShader

  • public class GVRUnlitVerticalStereoShader
extends GVRShaderTemplate
    Shader which samples from either the top or bottom half of a texture. This shader does not use light sources.

      • setMaterialDefaults

        protected void setMaterialDefaults(GVRShaderData material)
        Description copied from class: GVRShader
        Sets the default values for material data used by the shader. Subclasses can override this function to provide values for uniforms used by the material that are required by this shader. This function is called whenever a GVRMaterial is created that uses this shader class.
        Overrides:
        setMaterialDefaults in class GVRShader
        Parameters:
        material - the material whose values should be set
